audit_findings.title: Over-Committed Budget Categories
audit_findings.detail: Contingent Labor D1: Approved $1.589M but SOWs total $1.646M (Committed remainder = -$56,562). EDA Budget Capex: Approved $313K but SOWs total $873K (Committed remainder = -$559,722). More is committed than the approved allocation.

audit_findings.title: Flat Forecast Distribution
audit_findings.detail: Forecast monthly values use Committed / 12 (or / 11 for late starts). Categories like Travel, Training, and Marketing have lumpy real-world spending patterns. Consider seasonalizing these forecasts to improve monthly accuracy.

audit_findings.title: Forecast Not Yet Rolling Forward
audit_findings.detail: As actuals are booked, Forecast should update to reflect remaining spend: (Committed - YTD Actuals) / remaining months. Currently Forecast still uses the original Committed / 12 even for months with actuals.

audit_findings.title: Floating-Point Rounding Artifacts
audit_findings.detail: Some totals show sub-penny rounding differences due to division-based formulas. Wrapping key formulas in ROUND() would eliminate this.

audit_findings.title: Budget = Approved Plan (Fixed Baseline)
audit_findings.detail: Budget monthly columns correctly reference Approved FY26 / 12 on Budget rows and are blank on SOW rows. This establishes the approved plan as an immutable baseline for variance analysis.

audit_findings.title: Forecast = Committed Best Estimate
audit_findings.detail: Forecast monthly columns reference Committed FY26 / 12 on both Budget remainder rows and SOW rows. Budget vs Forecast variance now shows the gap between the approved plan and current committed spend expectations.

audit_findings.title: Unapproved Items Separated
audit_findings.detail: EDA Projects rows use 'Unapproved Budget' and 'Unapproved SOW' event types. These are excluded from approved budget rollups and shown separately in the dashboard as pending approval.

recommendations.title: Fix Over-Committed Categories
recommendations.detail: Contingent Labor D1 and EDA Budget Capex have negative Committed remainders. Either increase the Approved allocation or reduce SOW commitments to bring them back in balance.

recommendations.title: Roll Forecast Forward with Actuals
recommendations.detail: As monthly actuals are booked, update Forecast for remaining months to (Committed - YTD Actuals) / remaining months. This makes Forecast a living best estimate rather than a static plan.

recommendations.title: Seasonalize Forecast Allocations
recommendations.detail: Replace flat Committed/12 with realistic monthly profiles for lumpy categories: Travel (conference months), Training (Q1/Q3), project ramp-ups (phased milestones).
recommendations.impact: More accurate monthly Forecast vs Actual comparisons

recommendations.title: Add Percentage Variance Columns
recommendations.detail: Add (Budget - Actual) / Budget percentage columns alongside the existing dollar variance. Percentages contextualize the magnitude of variances across different-sized line items.

recommendations.title: Add Conditional Formatting in Excel
recommendations.detail: Apply green/yellow/red color coding in the spreadsheet: red for negative Committed remainders, traffic-light colors for Budget vs Actual thresholds (>10% under = green, 0-10% = yellow, over = red).
recommendations.impact: At-a-glance health indicators for budget status

recommendations.title: Add Forecast vs Actual Variance Section
recommendations.detail: Add a third variance section (Forecast - Actual) to measure forecasting accuracy. This completes the analysis triangle: Budget vs Actual, Budget vs Forecast, Forecast vs Actual.
recommendations.impact: Measures and improves forecasting accuracy over time

recommendations.title: Add Year-over-Year Comparison
recommendations.detail: Pull 2025 Budget actuals into a YoY delta view. The 2025 Budget tab already exists with historical data.
